# Contributing Guide

Thank you for your interest in contributing to the 75% Attendance Calculator! This guide will help you get started.

## Development Setup

1. **Fork and Clone**
   ```bash
   git clone https://github.com/bitcodeAShishcloud/attendance-calculator.git
   cd attendance-calculator
   ```

2. **Local Development**
   - No build process required - this is a static web application
   - Simply open `index.html` in your browser or use a local server
   - Recommended: Use VS Code with Live Server extension

## Project Structure

```
attendance-calculator/
├── index.html          # Main HTML file
├── app.js             # JavaScript functionality
├── style.css          # Styles and design system
├── README.md          # Project documentation
├── LICENSE            # MIT License
└── docs/              # Documentation files
    └── CONTRIBUTING.md # This file
```

## Code Style Guidelines

### HTML
- Use semantic HTML5 elements
- Include proper ARIA labels for accessibility
- Maintain consistent indentation (2 spaces)

### CSS
- Use CSS custom properties (variables) defined in `:root`
- Follow BEM-like naming conventions for components
- Maintain responsive design principles
- Support both light and dark themes

### JavaScript
- Use modern ES6+ features
- Maintain clear class structure
- Add comments for complex logic
- Handle errors gracefully
- Use descriptive variable names

## Feature Development

### Adding New Features
1. Create a new branch: `git checkout -b feature/your-feature-name`
2. Implement your changes
3. Test across different browsers and devices
4. Update documentation if needed
5. Submit a pull request

### Testing Checklist
- [ ] Works on desktop (Chrome, Firefox, Safari, Edge)
- [ ] Works on mobile devices
- [ ] Keyboard navigation works
- [ ] Screen reader compatibility
- [ ] Works with JavaScript disabled (graceful degradation)
- [ ] Print styles look good

## Accessibility Standards

This project follows WCAG 2.1 AA guidelines:
- Proper color contrast ratios
- Keyboard navigation support
- Screen reader compatibility
- Focus indicators
- Semantic markup

## Performance Considerations

- Keep bundle size minimal (currently ~50KB total)
- Optimize for fast loading on slow connections
- Use efficient CSS selectors
- Minimize DOM manipulations

## Browser Support

Target browsers:
- Chrome 88+
- Firefox 85+
- Safari 14+
- Edge 88+

## Reporting Issues

When reporting issues, please include:
- Browser and version
- Device type (desktop/mobile)
- Steps to reproduce
- Expected vs actual behavior
- Screenshots if relevant

## Pull Request Process

1. Ensure your code follows the style guidelines
2. Update documentation if needed
3. Test thoroughly
4. Write clear commit messages
5. Reference any related issues

## Questions?

Feel free to open an issue for any questions about contributing!
